 Mr Derrick Moore, the general manager, says this indicates mining in the open pit will last another 35 years - 'and then we might go underground'.
 Planning for the underground mine at Finsch started in the 1970s and the first work began in 1979.
 However, Mr Mark Button, mining superintendent, says: 'Finsch has come of age as an underground mine after two years.
 When, as occasionally happens, rock crashes on to the LHD trucks, it is relatively simply to haul the vehicles out virtually undamaged.
